Gunvald is in Annâk-khurfu in Elderslade.\n\nReturn to Gunvald.
Howlers' Notch

'Back for more, thief? You will steal no more of my cubs!

'My mate will get free, and he will tear you limb from limb!

'You will never find the cubs, [placeholder] filth.'

'Welcome back, friend! I heard you made a fine accounting of yourself! I am sorry you have been saddled with my duties, but am most glad that you are more than up to the task until I'm back on my feet.'

'Should you be up and about?' You ask him.

'My injuries are not grave, though they are keeping me from scouting for the time being. It was... suggested to me by Mother Amma that I make myself useful, so here I am, fletching arrows.'

'Good work, [placeholder]. The information you gathered will help when we push forward to reclaim Zarkul-sulûn.

'A scout returned while you were away with news of a Warg camp not far from where you found my clumsy brother. If you are still of a mind to help, make your way to Howlers' Notch and put down as many of those abominations as you can.

'Good luck! Oh, and, I've heard tell of a monstrous Warg in that area, so do be careful.'
Return to Gunvald
'The Wargs at Howlers' Notch are dangerous, and must be removed.'
Defeated the den mother

'You found and killed the pack and its leader? A grisly deed, to be sure, but we could not have the Wargs at our backs as we press forward to the wall.'
